==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Archbishop
<hw>Arch`bish"op</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>arcebisceop</ets>, <ets>arcebiscop</ets>, L.
<ets>archiepiscopus</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>'archiepi`skopos</grk>. See
<er>Bishop</er>.]</ety> <def>A chief bishop; a church dignitary of the
first class (often called a metropolitan or primate) who superintends
the conduct of the suffragan bishops in his province, and also exercises
episcopal authority in his own diocese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Archbishopric</ent>⟦br⟧
